commentary: Naveen-ul-Haq to Mosaddek Hossain, 1 run, OUT what a way for the innings to end. That was a full ball and slammed extremely hard by Mosaddek. The ball is racing away to the boundary but a brilliant save is made at the sweeper cover fence. They didn't run the first run as hard thinking it would carry to the boundary, and Mosaddek pushes Rubel to come across for the second to retain strike. The bowler collects the throw without fuss and takes the bails off at the non-striker's end and Rubel is well short of his crease

commentary: Mosaddek Hossain to Najibullah Zadran, no run Mushfiq has fluffed a simple stumping. Slower through the air, Najib stepped out for a leg-side slog, but was nowhere close to the pitch. commentary: Taskin Ahmed to Dawlat Zadran, FOUR runs Dawlat seals Afghanistan's thrilling win! They topple Bangladesh for the second time, having beaten the hosts earlier in the 2014 Asia Cup. Short of a length and outside off, Zadran swings for the hills and sends an outside edge over backward point
